free_txt: Reaction protons were observed with a 1 mm
thick surface barrier solid-state detector in
conjunction with a 512-channel analyzer and standard
detector electronics.
The relative error for the cross sections in the p0 and
p1 angular distributions is about 5% and is primarily
statistical. The p2 and p3 angular distributions have
an additional uncertainty introduced by the carbon
subtraction at forward angles. These forward-angle
measurements have a relative error of 15%. The absolute
cross sections have an estimated error of 20-25%. This
increased error is due in part to the normalization to
the deuteron elastic-scattering cross section, and in
part to the assumption that the latter have the
Rutherford value.

Targets were prepared by the reduction and subsequent
evaporation of the magnesium onto thin backings of
Formvar or gold. The thickness of the targets obtained
by this procedure was approximately 100-200 mu-g/cm2.
Magnesium oxide was enriched to 97-98% in 26Mg.
